            <h3>Question 3</h3>
            <ul>A: Storing passwords in a document in the cloud</ul>
            <ul>B: Using your network user ID as a password</ul>
            <ul>C: Using a password manager</ul>
            <ul>D: Applying two-factor authentication</ul>
            <ul>E: Using an OAuth where appropriate</ul>
            <ul>F: Using a friend's name in your password</ul>

            <p>Answer: A, B, F</p>
        </div>

        <div class="question"> 
            <h3>Question 4</h3>
            <ul>A: "Mine was a rabbit called Holly. That was back when I lived on Watts road."</ul>
            <ul>B: "I had a few pets myself. It's been so long, I can't remember I'm afraid."</ul>
            <ul>C: "I think her name was Holly. She was great but grew up to be massive!"</ul>

            <p>Answer: B</p>
        </div>

        <div class="question"> 
            <h3>Question 5</h3>
            <ul>A: Lock her computer</ul>
            <ul>B: Shutdown her computer and take the USB stick with her</ul>
            <ul>C: Store the USB stick in a secure place</ul>
            <ul>D: Wait for the file transfer to complete or cancel it</ul>
            <ul>E: Turn off her computer monitor</ul>
            <ul>F: Ask her colleague to watch the screen and press 'OK' when the transfer is done</ul>

            <p>Answer: A, B, E</p>
        </div>

        <div class="question"> 
            <h3>Question 6</h3>
            <ul>A: Tell them the information they're looking for</ul>
            <ul>B: Get up with all your belongings and talk to your colleague in the empty vestibule</ul>
            <ul>C: Explain that you're on a train and can't give them the information right now</ul>
            <ul>D: Keep your voice low and tell them some information but not all of it</ul>

            <p>Answer: A, C, D</p>
        </div>

